sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Adds tags to RDS resource.

Inputs:

  • Region - Region of the RDS resource.
  • Resource ARN - ARN of the resource
  • Tags - Key and Value pair to add tags.

Outputs:

  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure, Status is set to “Error”.
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Invalid resource name: "Provided resource name".
  • Missing Authentication Token.

(For information about the errors that are common to all actions, see Common Errors).

To use this action, a corresponding Amazon RDS credential must be created and associated with the Amazon RDS Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More
